Azure Table storage is a service that stores structured NoSQL data in the cloud, providing a key/attribute store with a schemaless design.

It&#39;s true if you have a java application using _that uses Apache Camel routing_ then the best choice would be to use the _CData JDBC Driver_ to work on Azure Tables.

Generally we use **Azure Tables client library** for Java Application to create tables, store your data, and perform CRUD operations on said data. Here you configure your app to access Table Storage by adding the following entry to your _pom.xml_ file&#39;s `dependencies` section :
```java
&lt;dependency&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;com.azure&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;azure-data-tables&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;12.1.1&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```
Then, add the following `import` statements to the top of the Java file where you want to use Azure Tables APIs to access tables.
```java
// Include the following imports to use table APIs
import com.azure.data.tables.TableClient;
import com.azure.data.tables.TableClientBuilder;
import com.azure.data.tables.TableServiceClient;
import com.azure.data.tables.TableServiceClientBuilder;
import com.azure.data.tables.models.ListEntitiesOptions;
import com.azure.data.tables.models.TableEntity;
import com.azure.data.tables.models.TableEntityUpdateMode;
import com.azure.data.tables.models.TableTransactionAction;
import com.azure.data.tables.models.TableTransactionActionType;
```

Alternatively, you can also use the **Cosmos DB with the Camel** which is also stores structured NoSQL data in the cloud. There is also the [AZURE COSMOSDB](https://camel.apache.org/components/3.11.x/azure-cosmosdb-component.html) document at Camel website which explains its components. So you can also use Cosmos DB Table API in your Java application.

Read the [How to use the Azure Tables client library for Java](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/table/how-to-use-java#configure-your-app-to-access-table-storage) document for more detailed information on how to use Table API and Cosmos DB API with Java.

